- Irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure: 5.95%  
- Irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure: 7.15%  
- Let the percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure be \( x \).  
Then, 5.95% + 7.15% + \( x \) = 17%.  
Solving: \( x = 17\% - 5.95\% - 7.15\% = 17\% - 13.10\% = 3.90\% \).  

Now, the percentage with low blood pressure is 19%, which includes those with both irregular and regular heartbeat. Thus, the percentage with both regular heartbeat and low blood pressure is:  
19% (total LBP) - 3.90% (LBP and IH) = 15.10%.  

