Use the $D_0$ value of $\mathrm{H}_2(4.478 \mathrm{eV})$ and the $D_0$ value of $\mathrm{H}_2^{+}(2.651 \mathrm{eV})$ to calculate the first ionization energy of $\mathrm{H}_2$ (that is, the energy needed to remove an electron from $\mathrm{H}_2$ ). The unit of the answer should be  $\mathrm{eV}$.

Output:

