The probability \(P(D > 0)\) is computed by standardizing:  
\[P(D > 0) = P\left(Z > \frac{0 - (-1)}{5}\right) = P(Z > 0.2),\]  
where \(Z \sim N(0, 1)\). Using the standard normal distribution, \(P(Z \leq 0.2) \approx 0.5793\), so:  
