Solution: The function \(f(x) = c x^3 (1 - x)^6\) for \(0 < x < 1\) must integrate to 1 to be a probability density function. Thus, the integral \(\int_{0}^{1} c x^3 (1 - x)^6  dx = 1\) must hold. Solving for \(c\):

\[
