\]

The integral \(\int_{0}^{1} x^3 (1 - x)^6  dx\) corresponds to the beta function \(B(4, 7)\), which evaluates to \(\frac{1}{840}\). Therefore:

\[
c = \frac{1}{\frac{1}{840}} = 840
\]

