- 19% have low blood pressure (LBP).  
- 17% have an irregular heartbeat (IH).  
- Of those with irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure is 35% of 17% = 0.35 × 17 = 5.95%.  
- Of those with normal blood pressure (NBP), 11% have irregular heartbeat. First, normal blood pressure percentage is 100% - 16% (HBP) - 19% (LBP) = 65%. Thus, the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure is 11% of 65% = 0.11 × 65 = 7.15%.  

The total percentage with irregular heartbeat is the sum of those with irregular heartbeat and high, normal, or low blood pressure:  
- Irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure: 5.95%  
- Irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure: 7.15%  
- Let the percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure be \( x \).  
Then, 5.95% + 7.15% + \( x \) = 17%.  
Solving: \( x = 17\% - 5.95\% - 7.15\% = 17\% - 13.10\% = 3.90\% \).  

Now, the percentage with low blood pressure is 19%, which includes those with both irregular and regular heartbeat. Thus, the percentage with both regular heartbeat and low blood pressure is:  
19% (total LBP) - 3.90% (LBP and IH) = 15.10%.  

